1 5. "Lead carrier" means the insurance company selected by the board to administer the
2 association benefit plans.
3 26.1 - 08.1 - 02. Cessation of operations .
4 1. The association shall cease enrollment under the plan effective May 1, 2025 .
5 2. After taking all reasonable steps, including those specified in this section, to timely and
6 efficiently assist in the transition of individuals receiving benefits under chapter
7 26.1 - 08, and paying health insurance claims for plan coverage and meeting all other
8 obligations of the board under this section, the association shall cease operating the
9 pool.
10 3. The association may take any action it deems necessary to:
11 a. Cease enrollment for plan coverage effective May 1, 2025 .
12 b. Terminate all existing benefit plans effective December 31, 2025 .
13 c. Provide at least a ninety-day notice to current policyholders of the termination.
14 4. This section does not require the board to revise plan benefits to comply with this
15 chapter.
16 26.1 - 08.1 - 03. Board of directors .
17 1. Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter, to facilitate an efficient cessation
18 of operations, the board:
19 a. May continue to use the lead carrier to fulfill administrative tasks and operations.
20 b. Shall continue to follow the requirements of participating members under section
21 26.1 - 08 - 09 .
22 c. May implement a process to assess members based on actual program costs
23 rather than projected program costs.
24 2. If the board has excess funds after cessation of operations of the association, the
25 funds must be returned by the lead carrier to the insurer assessed under section
26 26.1 - 08 - 09 .
27 26.1 - 08.1 - 04. Enrollment of individuals losing creditable coverage .
28 An individual losing creditable coverage must be provided enrollment into a comparable:
29 1. Health benefit plan; or
30 2. Plan under a Medicare supplement policy that has a benefit package classified as
31 plan A, B, C, F (including F with a high deductible), G, K, or L under guaranteed issue .
